column15: In Spring 2025, the university enrolled 2,319 students overall, with women (W) outnumbering men (M). CLASS (College of Liberal Arts & Social Sciences) enrolled 703 students, SEST (School of Engineering, Science, & Technology) had 608, BS (School of Business) had 455, CHRS (College of Health & Rehabilitation Sciences) enrolled 293, and ED (School of Education) had 260. Degree codes include BA/BS (Bachelor of Arts/Science), MA/MS (Master of Arts/Science), MBA (Master of Business Administration), BGS (Bachelor of General Studies), ED.D (Doctor of Education), DNAP (Doctor of Nurse Anesthesia Practice), GRADCERT/OCP (Graduate or Post-BA Certificate), and SYC/PM CERT (Sixth Year/Post-Master’s Certificate).
